First Lady Melania Trump celebrated National Read Across America Day and Dr. Seuss' birthday by visiting the Phyllis and David Komansky Center for Children's Health at NewYork-Presbyterian/Weill Cornell Medical Center. She met with doctors, families, and patients and shared the joy of reading with children. Melania Trump brought a package of Dr. Seuss books, including her and her son's favorite, "Oh, The Places You'll Go!" She read to children in the pediatrics playroom and emphasized the importance of early reading in becoming lifelong learners. Melania Trump praised Dr. Seuss for bringing joy, laughter, and inspiration to children's lives while teaching them to read, dream, and care. She also highlighted the importance of education and reading in achieving empowerment and equal opportunities.